    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a clear focus on speed and high-ceiling matchups. **Kyle Tucker** (77.06) and **Jackson Merrill** (74.85) headline our starting nine, benefiting from favorable conditions against Taillon and Alcantara respectively. **Kyle Tucker** is in an elite spot, aided by an out-blowing wind and a prime #4 lineup slot, while **Jackson Merrill** leverages a +10% order bonus as the leadoff man. Our most aggressive play in the SB-starved landscape is **Josh Lowe** (71.68); while his base projection is modest, his +14% platoon edge and the slow delivery of the opposing pitcher create a significant opportunity for stolen base production that outweighs his neutral park factors.\n\nThe decision to bench **Miguel Vargas** (58.95) was the most difficult call of the morning. While he holds a respectable projection against the lefty Kikuchi, he ultimately fell short of the efficiency floor established by **Josh Jung** (59.39) and **Marcell Ozuna** (60.22). We are forced to navigate significant risk at catcher, where **Drake Baldwin** (46.72) draws the toughest assignment of the day against Skubal\u2019s 2.71 xERA; though the -19% SP skill penalty is brutal, we are holding firm to preserve our games-played cap. As always, keep an eye on the status of our rotation, as the rainout for **Gunnar Henderson** has forced an immediate shuffling of our infield depth to keep our production as consistent as possible.",
